Package org.semanticweb.vlog4j.core.model.api

Interface Atom

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AtomImpl
    public interface Atom
    Interface for atoms. An atom is predicate applied to a tuple of terms; that is, an atomic formula is a formula of the form P(t1,...,tn) for P a Predicate name, and t1,...,tn some Terms. The number of terms in the tuple corresponds to the Predicate arity.
    Author:
    david.carral@tu-dresden.de
